summary: This document details a meeting on August 2, 2019, between FBI Special Agent Kelly Maguire and Frank Senerchia regarding the return of property belonging to Jeffrey Epstein. Senerchia, representing Epstein's legal counsel, took custody of various items released by the FBI that were deemed non-relevant to the investigation.

keyFacts: Frank Senerchia was tasked by Epstein's legal counsel to retrieve property from the FBI.
The property included various items such as cash, jewelry, and watches.
Senerchia signed two FD-597 Receipt for Property forms upon receiving the items.
The meeting took place at the FBI office in New York City.
